						<summary>

						<p>Pillar with the <hi rend="italic">dvārapāla</hi> image in the Śiva temple.</p>						

						<p>The inscription has no date. On the basis of palaeography it may be assigned to 14th century A.D.</p>						

						<p>It records the gift of the image of the <hi rend="italic">dvārapālaka,</hi> obviously on which the epigraph is engraved by Appā-battuḍu, who was an <hi rend="italic">agasāla</hi> (gold smith) of Koppartti and son of Tāḍigōṭula Tippā-bhattuḍu.</p>						

						</summary>
